<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<org.eclipse.epf.uma:ContentDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-tNMtDSxLuZDmIgMSaI8csg" name="reviewing_product_lifecycle_data_with_fp,_P3amIP7hEd2pf77DabzLMA" guid="-tNMtDSxLuZDmIgMSaI8csg" changeDate="2009-10-19T09:42:07.146-0700" version="7.5.0">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The examples in this tool mentor are based on the Product Portfolio Management, Version 1.0, add-on and IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg;&#xD;
    Focal Point&amp;trade;, Version 6.4. If you use the add-on, most of the necessary modules and views have already been configured&#xD;
    for you. If you are not using the add-on, your workspace will require some configuration to support the features&#xD;
    described in this tool mentor.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Configuration&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    First, configure Rational Focal Point with the attributes needed for the product's lifecycle review by following these&#xD;
    steps:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ol>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Create a module to store your product data and name it, for example, &quot;Products.&quot;&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Create the necessary attributes:&lt;br />&#xD;
        &lt;br />&#xD;
        &lt;table title=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;2&quot; width=&quot;78%&quot;>&#xD;
            &lt;tbody>&#xD;
                &lt;tr>&#xD;
                    &lt;th abbr=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;21%&quot; scope=&quot;col&quot;>&#xD;
                        Attribute Name&#xD;
                    &lt;/th>&#xD;
                    &lt;th abbr=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;20%&quot; scope=&quot;col&quot;>&#xD;
                        Attribute Type&#xD;
                    &lt;/th>&#xD;
                    &lt;th abbr=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;59%&quot; scope=&quot;col&quot;>&#xD;
                        Description&#xD;
                    &lt;/th>&#xD;
                &lt;/tr>&#xD;
                &lt;tr>&#xD;
                    &lt;td>&#xD;
                        Product Name&#xD;
                    &lt;/td>&#xD;
                    &lt;td>&#xD;
                        Text&#xD;
                    &lt;/td>&#xD;
                    &lt;td>&#xD;
                        &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
                    &lt;/td>&#xD;
                &lt;/tr>&#xD;
                &lt;tr>&#xD;
                    &lt;td>&#xD;
                        Lifecycle Phase&#xD;
                    &lt;/td>&#xD;
                    &lt;td>&#xD;
                        Choice&#xD;
                    &lt;/td>&#xD;
                    &lt;td>&#xD;
                        For example: Introduced, Growth, Maturity, Decline&#xD;
                    &lt;/td>&#xD;
                &lt;/tr>&#xD;
                &lt;tr>&#xD;
                    &lt;td>&#xD;
                        Actual Revenue&#xD;
                    &lt;/td>&#xD;
                    &lt;td>&#xD;
                        Matrix&#xD;
                    &lt;/td>&#xD;
                    &lt;td>&#xD;
                        Use a matrix attribute to capture financial data by product, such as revenue or cost&#xD;
                    &lt;/td>&#xD;
                &lt;/tr>&#xD;
            &lt;/tbody>&#xD;
        &lt;/table>&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Create a display to make the data accessible to your users.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ol>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    See the &quot;Configure&quot; section in Focal Point Help for further details on how to create workspaces, modules, attributes,&#xD;
    and views.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Review products by lifecycle phase&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Portfolio managers&amp;nbsp;are interested in following up on how the products in the portfolio distribute over the&#xD;
    lifecycle phases. To do this, follow these steps:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ol>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Log in to Rational Focal Point, if you are not already logged in.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Open the &lt;strong>Workspace&lt;/strong>.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Select &lt;strong>Display &amp;gt; Our Product Portfolio (r/w).&lt;/strong>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Select the &lt;strong>Statistical display&lt;/strong>&amp;nbsp;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;./resources/stat_display.jpg&quot; width=&quot;20&quot;&#xD;
        height=&quot;20&quot; /> button in the toolbar.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Finally, select which attributes to display at the bottom of the page.&amp;nbsp;In this case, select &quot;Lifecycle Phase&quot;&#xD;
        in &lt;strong>Row&lt;/strong>, &quot;None&quot; in &lt;strong>Column&lt;/strong>, and &quot;Number of Elements&quot; in &lt;strong>Cell&lt;/strong>.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        In the result window, you will see how the products distribute over the different lifecycle phases presented in&#xD;
        percentage and in absolute value.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ol>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Review revenue by lifecycle phase and products&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Using the same &lt;strong>Statistical display&lt;/strong> as in the previous example, you can view different types of&#xD;
    financial information (as long as the types are included in the view definition). For example, if you want to review&#xD;
    the actual revenue for all products, in &lt;strong>Cell&lt;/strong>, select &quot;Sum: Actual Revenue,&quot; instead. The data in the&#xD;
    cells is then summarized from all products for that lifecycle phase.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;img alt=&quot;Product lifecycle data selections&quot; src=&quot;./resources/prod_lc_data.jpg&quot; />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    If you want to view the actual revenue data for a particular product, click the product link in the result view.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ContentDescription>
